## 1. VS Code

Download and install VS Code from <https://code.visualstudio.com/download>.
After installation, open the project and install recommended extensions when
prompted.

---

## 2. Git

Install git following the instructions for your platform.

Verify:

```zsh
git --version
```

---

## 3. Python and UV

Install UV and Python:

```zsh
curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh
uv python install {{ python_version }}
```

Verify:

```zsh
uv python find {{ python_version }}
```

---

## 4. Bun

Install Bun:

```zsh
curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash
```

Verify:

```zsh
bun --version
```

---

## 5. Container Runtime

Install {{ container_runtime }} following the
[official instructions]({% if container_runtime == 'docker' %}https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/{% else %}https://podman.io/docs/installation{% endif %}).

Verify:

```zsh
{{ container_runtime }} --version
{{ container_runtime }} compose version
```

---

## 6. Task Runner

Install [Task](https://taskfile.dev):

```zsh
sh -c "$(curl --location https://taskfile.dev/install.sh)" -- -d -b ~/.local/bin
```

Verify:

```zsh
task --version
```

---

## 7. Clone and Setup

```zsh
git clone <REPO_URL> {{ project_slug }}
cd {{ project_slug }}
task setup
```

This command will:
- Create Python virtual environment
- Install backend dependencies (`uv sync`)
- Install frontend dependencies (`bun install`)
{%- if use_playwright %}
- Install Playwright browsers (`bunx playwright install --with-deps chromium`)
{%- endif %}
- Set up pre-commit hooks
- Copy `.env.example` to `.env`

For non-local runs, create environment files from `.env.example` as needed:

```zsh
cp .env.example .env.dev
cp .env.example .env.test
cp .env.example .env.staging
cp .env.example .env.prod
```

Then apply the environment-specific deltas listed in the
**Per-Environment Quick Reference** section at the bottom of `.env.example`.

Local-only overrides:

- backend/global: `.env.local` (start from `.env.local.example`)
- frontend: `frontend/.env.local` (start from `frontend/.env.local.example`)

---

## 8. Start Development

```zsh
task dev
```

Visit:
- Backend API: <http://localhost:8000>
{%- if api_style in ('rest', 'both') %}
- API docs: <http://localhost:8000/api/docs>
{%- endif %}
{%- if api_style in ('graphql', 'both') %}
- GraphiQL IDE: <http://localhost:8000/graphql>
{%- endif %}
- Frontend: <http://localhost:3000>
{%- if use_ai %}

---


If AI features are enabled, additional setup is required:

```zsh
task backend:ai:setup
```

This validates AI dependencies and creates data directories.

Set the required environment variables in `.env`:

{% if use_ai %}
```env
{{ project_slug | upper }}_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
```
{% endif %}
{% if use_azure_openai %}
```env
{{ project_slug | upper }}_AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.openai.azure.com/
{{ project_slug | upper }}_AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=...
{{ project_slug | upper }}_AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=your-deployment
```
{% endif %}
{% if use_knowledge_graph %}

For Neo4j (if using `neo4j` backend):

```zsh
# macOS/Linux
scripts/install/install-neo4j.zsh
# Windows (PowerShell) — or use the bundled compose profile
{{ container_runtime }} compose --profile knowledge-graph up -d neo4j
```
{% endif %}
{% if use_faiss %}

For FAISS:

```zsh
# macOS/Linux
scripts/install/install-faiss.zsh
# Windows — install via uv
uv pip install faiss-cpu
```
{% endif %}
{% if use_mcp %}

MCP server will be available at <http://localhost:8000/mcp> once `{{ project_slug | upper }}_MCP_ENABLED=true` is set.
{% endif %}

See [CONFIG.md](CONFIG.md) for the full list of AI configuration variables.
{%- endif %}
